title: NA
organism_ch1: peripheral blood derived CD34+ progenitor cells
molecule_ch1: CD34+   were isolated directly from the peripheral blood of the patients using CD34-MicroBead-Kit (Miltenyi Biotec) according to the manufacturer’s protocol
label_ch1: Total RNA was extracted with miRNeasy Kit (Qiagen) following the manufacturer's recommendations
taxid_ch1: RNA sample were sent to Exiqon (Vedbaek, Denmark) for labelling for miRCURYTM LNA Array microRNA profiling.
data_processing.1: Data was processed by Exiqon as standard data analysis:
data_processing.2: For the normalization of the data it was used the geomean of all assays detected in all 18 samples.   The formula used is:  Normalized Cp = Geomean(n=18) – assay Cp.
data_processing.3: The average normalized Cp of the samples in test groups and in a control group has been calculated.
data_processing.4: ΔΔCp: The difference in normalized Cps has been calculated between the average normalized Cp of test and control sample groups.
platform_id: Fold change = 2 ΔΔCp: Difference in normalized Cps (ΔΔCp) has been converted to fold change with  2 ΔΔCp.  A fold change > 1 indicate up-regulation and a fold change < 1 indicate down-regulation in test (sCAD- or STEMI d0- or STEMI d5-) sample group compared to contol (healthy control) sample group.
